; Lock in the "self-contained binary" guarantee: on `dune test` this inspects a real linked artifact
; (the ffi test executable, which pulls in fennec-mongo.ffi and therefore the full static C link
; line) and fails if it depends on any non-system shared library. Runs everywhere dune does — no
; mongod or network needed. When the driver degraded (HAVE_MONGOC=0) the binary links no libmongoc
; at all, so it trivially passes too.
(rule
 (alias runtest)
 (deps
  check.sh
  ../ffi/test/test_ffi.exe)
 (action
  (run bash check.sh %{dep:../ffi/test/test_ffi.exe})))
